PHASE 3 BEHAVIOR VERIFIED
- Simple-base slots are independent from the major-base limit and equal civilization level.
- Civilization Lv.0 has no simple-base slot; Lv.1 through Lv.4 allow one through four.
- A living simple base has 40 HP and a 50 m construction radius.
- Current-position construction remains 85 m even while standing directly on a simple base.
- Placement requires fresh accurate GPS, a road intersection within 50 m, 140 m owned-base separation and 120 m hostile-base separation.
- Existing secondary bases from older saves remain major bases.
- The current assault squad can deploy from a living simple base; destroyed simple bases cannot deploy.
- Enemies attack a simple base when it is meaningfully closer than the city, but do not divert from a much nearer city.
- Destruction removes construction, deployment and regional-activity benefits.
- A destroyed site retains its slot, remains visible as a ruin and requires onsite rebuilding within 50 m.
- Major bases cannot overwrite active or destroyed simple-base sites.
- Save/restore retains simple-base gameplay state without exact GPS metadata.

ISSUES FOUND AND CORRECTED
1. When the player stood exactly on a simple base, duplicate-anchor suppression removed the independent 85 m player-position radius and reduced construction to 50 m. The player and simple-base anchors now coexist.
2. Major-base placement originally ignored simple-base sites. Active and destroyed simple-base sites now enforce the existing 220 m major-base separation rule.
3. Enemy settlement routing was verified and constrained so a distant simple base does not irrationally pull enemies away from a nearby city.
4. Destroyed simple bases were explicitly removed from remote high-frequency simulation anchors while retaining their rebuild site and slot.

